Toss chicken with flour in plastic bag or bowl. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet over medium-high heat; cook chicken 2 minutes on each side or until golden. Remove from skillet. Add remaining oil to skillet; saute mushrooms, onion and garlic 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in broth, tomato paste, undrained stewed tomatoes, Italian herb seasoning, salt and pepper. Bring to boil; reduce heat. Add chicken; simmer 4 to 5 minutes.